title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows applications to connect to paired bluetooth devices.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.FLASHLIGHT.description: Allows the application to control the flashlight.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

manifest_analysis.title:
Broadcast Receiver (com.google.android.gcm.GCMBroadcastReceiver) is Protected by a permission, but the protection level of the permission should be checked.
Permission: com.google.android.c2dm.permission.SEND
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

metadata.description: Query Database of SMS, Contacts etc

CWE-312 Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive informations like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.
The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.

metadata.description: This App may have root detection capabilities.
App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.

playstore_details.title: OTP SmartBank
playstore_details.description:
Using OTP Bank’s Smartbank android application, you can easily access OTP Bank’s electronic banking services: domestic Hungarian Forint transfer, OTP Bank’s ATM and branch locator, foreign currency exchange rates, QR authentication. In addition you may use the moneychanger.  

Technical requirements:  
- OS: 4.1 or higher Android phone or tablet
- Device: min. 240x320 resolution, min. 512 MB RAM
- Mobile design for tablets
- Touch ID authentication can be used on all devices that support Google fingerprint API

In the case of rooted devices, the SmartBank application's new version is not available.


OTP SmartBank

In order to access SmartBank, you will need to register in the application after downloading and opening the application. To register, you will need to use Mobile signature for the internet service. During the registration your internetbank identifier and a 6-8 digit PIN code is needed. The PIN code can be substituted by a fingerprint if the device is capable for that. To finish the registration a numeric code (sent by SMS) is necessary.

In case QR scanning function does not work on the device on which you have completed a new registration, please visit the following website for more information: https://www.otpbank.hu/portal/hu/SmartBank/Regisztracio

Functions (retail and corporate bank accounts and credit card accounts)

- Account details 
- Account history
- Check transactions
- Sign transactions (for corporate accounts)
- Time deposits (details and early mature)
- New time deposit
- Domestic Forint transfers 
- Foreign currency transfers 
- Card-to-card transfers (for retail accounts)
- Future transfers
- Cheque scanning
- Bill payments: „Díjnet”, „Csekkrendező” (for retail accounts)
- Motorway ticket
- Mobile phone top-up
- Online purchase
- Bankcard details, changing limits, activation, blockage and webCARD details (for retail accounts)
- „Vásárlási kedvezmények” registration, offers, query
- Settings: blocking access, changing password, enable multitasking, profile settings
- Saving and deleting templates
- Renaming accounts
- Repeating transactions
- Sharing transaction details
- Messages
